# Testing — {{TEST_FRAMEWORK}}

## TEST STRUCTURE
- Unit tests: colocated — `{{SOURCE_FILE}}.test.{{EXT}}` next to source
- Integration tests: `{{INTEGRATION_TEST_DIR}}/`
- E2E tests: `{{E2E_TEST_DIR}}/` using {{E2E_FRAMEWORK}}

## COMMANDS
- Run all: `{{CMD_TEST}}`
- Watch: `{{CMD_TEST_WATCH}}`
- Coverage: `{{CMD_TEST_COVERAGE}}`
- Single file: `{{CMD_TEST}} {{TEST_FILE_FLAG}} path/to/file`

## TEST PATTERNS
- DO: Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA) structure — blank line between sections
- DO: Descriptive names — `it('returns 404 when user not found')`
- DO: Test behavior, not implementation — call public API, not internals
- DO NOT: Share mutable state between tests — isolate in `beforeEach`

## MOCKING STRATEGY
- External APIs: {{MOCK_STRATEGY}}
<!-- MOCK_STRATEGY example: "Mock at HTTP layer with msw — never mock individual fetch calls" -->
- Database: {{DB_MOCK_STRATEGY}}
<!-- DB_MOCK_STRATEGY example: "Real test database via Docker — no in-memory fakes (burned us before)" -->
- Time: `{{TIME_MOCK_APPROACH}}`
<!-- TIME_MOCK_APPROACH example: "vi.useFakeTimers() — never new Date() in tests" -->

## COVERAGE TARGETS
- Minimum: {{COVERAGE_THRESHOLD}}%
- Enforce via: `{{COVERAGE_ENFORCEMENT}}`
<!-- COVERAGE_ENFORCEMENT example: "vitest --coverage --coverage.thresholds.lines=80" -->

## FACTORIES / FIXTURES
- Test factories in: `{{TEST_FACTORIES_PATH}}`
- DO: Use factories for complex objects — NEVER inline large object literals
